title: RX-78-2 Gundam
info_text: The RX-78-2 Gundam (aka the Gundam or White Mobile Suit) is the titular mobile suit of Mobile Suit Gundam. Part of the RX-78 Gundam series, it was built in secret on Side 7. The Gundam would turn the tide of war in favor of the Earth Federation during the One Year War against the Principality of Zeon. The unit was primarily piloted by the series' main protagonist Amuro Ray.

title: MS-06S Zaku II Commander Type (Char Aznable custom)
info_text: The MS-06S Zaku II Commander Type is a Mobile Suit introduced in the Mobile Suit Gundam television series. This variant looks very similar to the standard MS-06F Zaku II, so much so, that the Earth Federation can generally only tell the difference from color schemes most pilots apply to their units and the increased performance of this version.

title: MS-06F/J Zaku II
info_text: The MS-06F Zaku II is one of many variants of the MS-06 Zaku II series of Mobile Suits. The MS-06F was the most produced mobile suit during the One Year War, with 3,246 units built during the war. The MS-06F was piloted by top-scoring Zeon MS aces, as well as by the highest-scoring Zeon ace in the war. It first appears in the anime series Mobile Suit Gundam.

title: RX-78-3 Gundam "G-3"
info_text: The RX-78-3 Gundam "G-3" is a variation of the original RX-78-2 Gundam. It first appeared as part of Mobile Suit Variations model kit series, designed by Kunio Okawara and later reappeared in the game Gundam Battle Universe and Gundam the Ride: A Baoa Qu.

title: MSZ-006 Zeta Gundam
info_text:
The MSΖ-006 Zeta Gundam (MSΖ-006 Ζ
ゼータ
ガンダム?) is the titular mobile suit of the Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam television series and also featured in the Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ television series. It was most famously piloted by its designer, Kamille Bidan during the Gryps War.

title: MS-06R-1 Zaku II (Shin Matsunaga custom)
info_text: The MS-06R-1A Zaku II High Mobility Type is a mobile suit first appearing in Mobile Suit Variations for Mobile Suit Gundam III: Encounters in Space. It is a mass-production space combat mobile suit, and one of many variants of the standard MS-06 Zaku II.

title: MS-06R-2 Zaku II (Johnny Ridden custom)
info_text: The MS-06R-2 Zaku II High Mobility Type is a limited production space combat mobile suit, and is another high mobility version of the MS-06 Zaku II. It was first featured in the original design series Mobile Suit Variations (MSV).

title: MS-14S Gelgoog Commander Type (Char Aznable Custom)
info_text: The MS-14S (YMS-14) Gelgoog Commander Type is a commander mobile suit that entered production as the MS-14A Gelgoog.

title: MS-14B/C Gelgoog High Mobility Type/Gelgoog Cannon (Johnny Ridden Custom)
info_text: The MS-14C Gelgoog Cannon (ゲルググキャノン, Gerugugukyanon) is a mass-produced artillery mobile suit. It is a variant of the original MS-14A Gelgoog. It is featured in the original design series Mobile Suit Variations (MSV).

title: RX-78GP01 Gundam "Zephyranthes"
info_text: The RX-78GP01 Gundam "Zephyranthes" (aka Zephyranthes, GP01, Unit 1) is a prototype general-purpose mobile suit from the OVA series Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory. It was piloted by Kou Uraki for the Earth Federation Forces during Operation Stardust.

title: MS-14A Gelgoog
info_text: The MS-14A Gelgoog (ゲルググ,Gerugugu) was the last mass production mobile suit produced by the Principality of Zeon during the One Year War.

title: RX-78GP01-Fb Gundam Full Burnern "Zephyranthes"
info_text: The RX-78GP01-Fb Gundam "Zephyranthes" Full Burnern (Often translated as Gundam "Zephyranthes" Full Vernian) is the upgraded space use version of the RX-78GP01 Gundam "Zephyranthes". Featured in the anime OVA series Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory, it is piloted by Kou Uraki.

title: RX-78GP02A Gundam "Physalis"
info_text: The RX-78GP02A Gundam "Physalis" (aka "Physalis", GP02A) is the second of four mobile suits in the Gundam Development Project and featured in Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory. It originally belonged to Earth Federation until it was stolen and piloted by Delaz Fleet's ace pilot, Anavel Gato.

title: RX-178 Gundam Mk-II (A.E.U.G. colors)
info_text: The RX-178 Gundam Mk-II is a mobile suit that appears in the anime series Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam. It is a successor of the famous RX-78-2 Gundam that served in the One Year War with cheaper armor to reduce costs.

title: RX-178 Gundam Mk-II (Titans colors)
info_text: The RX-178 Gundam Mk-II is a mobile suit that appears in the anime series Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam. It is a successor of the famous RX-78-2 Gundam that served in the One Year War with cheaper armor to reduce costs.

title: RX-178+FXA-05D Super Gundam
info_text: The RX-178+FXA-05D Super Gundam is a mobile suit in the series Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam. It is the combination of the FXA-05D G-Defenser and the RX-178 Gundam Mk-II. It was piloted by Emma Sheen.

title: RGM-79 GM
info_text: The RGM-79 GM (aka GM, pronounced Jim) was the first mass-produced mobile suit of the Earth Federation. It first appears in Mobile Suit Gundam.

title: MS-05B Zaku I
info_text: The MS-05B Zaku I is a mobile suit line from the Universal Century time-line.

title: MS-05B Zaku I (Black Tri-Stars Version)
info_text: The MS-05B Zaku I is a mobile suit line from the Universal Century time-line.

title: MS-06R-1A Zaku II (Black Tri-Stars Version)
info_text: The MS-06R-1A Zaku II High Mobility Type is a mobile suit first appearing in Mobile Suit Variations for Mobile Suit Gundam III: Encounters in Space. It is a mass-production space combat mobile suit, and one of many variants of the standard MS-06 Zaku II.

title: MS-09 Dom
info_text: The MS-09B Dom is a mass-production ground combat mobile suit which first appears in Mobile Suit Gundam. It is most well known to be piloted by the Black Tri-Stars, along with the pilots Abraham and Rayburn.

title: RX-78NT-1 Gundam NT-1
series: Mobile Suit Gundam 0080: War in the Pocket
info_text: The RX-78NT-1 Gundam "Alex" (RX-78NT-1 ガンダム「アレックス」 RX-78NT-1 Gandamu Arekkusu?, "Alex" being an acronym for "Armored Layers EXperimental") is the main mobile suit featured in the Mobile Suit Gundam 0080: War in the Pocket OVA. It was a next generation Gundam the Earth Federation developed during the One Year War for Newtypes. Christina Mackenzie served as its test pilot.

title: MS-09R Rick Dom
info_text: The MS-09R Rick Dom (リック・ドム Rikku Domu?) is a mass production space combat mobile suit, and variant of the MS-09B Dom. It was first featured in the anime series Mobile Suit Gundam.

title: RGM-79N GM Custom
info_text: The RGM-79N GM Custom is a limited-production general-purpose mobile suit, that first appeared in Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory.

title: RGM-79Q GM Quel
info_text: The RGM-79Q GM Quel is a mass-produced general purpose mobile suit used by the Earth Federation's elite Titans special unit. It first appeared in the OVA Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory and was later featured in Advance of Zeta: The Flag of Titans and Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam: A New Translation.

title: MSZ-010 ΖΖ Gundam
info_text: The MSZ-010 ΖΖ Gundam (aka ΖΖ Gundam, ZZ, MSZ-010; pronounced "Double Zeta") is the titular mobile suit of the anime Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ. It is piloted by Judau Ashta.

title: RX-79(G) Gundam Ground Type
series: Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team
info_text: The RX-79[G] Gundam Ground Type (陸戦型ガンダム) is a limited mass production Gundam-type mobile suit that was the beginning of the ground based RX-79 series of mobile suits. The unit is first featured in Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team.

title: RX-78-2 Gundam Ver. 1.5
info_text: The RX-78-2 Gundam (aka the Gundam or White Mobile Suit) is the titular mobile suit of Mobile Suit Gundam. Part of the RX-78 Gundam series, it was built in secret on Side 7. The Gundam would turn the tide of war in favor of the Earth Federation during the One Year War against the Principality of Zeon. The unit was primarily piloted by the series' main protagonist Amuro Ray.

title: MSN-04 Sazabi
info_text: The MSN-04 Sazabi is a mobile suit that appears in Mobile Suit Gundam: Char's Counterattack. It is piloted by Char Aznable.

title: FA-010S Full Armor ZZ Gundam
info_text: The FA-010S (FA-010B) Full Armor ZZ Gundam is a mobile suit that appears in Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ. It is an upgrade of the MSZ-010S Enhanced ZZ Gundam.

title: MS-05B Zaku I (Ramba Ral Custom)
info_text: The MS-05B Zaku I is a mobile suit line from the Universal Century time-line.

title: MS-07B Gouf
info_text: The MS-07B Gouf is a mass production ground close-quarters combat mobile suit. It was first featured in the anime series Mobile Suit Gundam.

title: RX-79[G]Ez8 Gundam Ez8
series: Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team
info_text: The RX-79[G]Ez-8 Gundam Ez8 (ガンダムEz8) is a custom variant of the original RX-79［G］ Gundam Ground Type. It was one of the signature mobile suits in the 12-episode anime OVA series Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team piloted by the series' main protagonist Shiro Amada.

title: RX-93 ν Gundam
info_text: The RX-93 ν Gundam (aka Nu Gundam, Nu) is a mobile suit that appears in Mobile Suit Gundam: Char's Counterattack. It was designed and piloted by Amuro Ray.

title: MS-18E Kämpfer
series: Mobile Suit Gundam 0080: War in the Pocket
info_text: MS-18 Kämpfer (ケンプファー Kenpufā?) is a heavy assault mobile suit featured in the Mobile Suit Gundam 0080: War in the Pocket OVA. It was used by the Principality of Zeon during the One Year War.

title: MS-07B-3 Gouf Custom
series: Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team
info_text: The MS-07B-3 Gouf Custom is an upgraded variant of the MS-07B Gouf that was introduced shortly after the MS-09B Dom. It first appeared in the anime Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team.

title: MSN-00100 Hyaku Shiki
info_text: The MSN-00100 (MSN-100, MSN-001) Hyaku Shiki is a prototype attack use Mobile Suit from the Universal Century timeline. The unit was featured in Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam and Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ. It was primarily piloted by Quattro Bajeena during the Gryps Conflict and later Beecha Oleg in the First Neo Zeon War.

title: RX-78GP03S Gundam "Dendrobium Stamen"
info_text: The RX-78GP03S Gundam "Dendrobium Stamen" (aka Stamen, GP03S) is a prototype space attack use mobile suit. It was first seen in Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory and was piloted by Kou Uraki.

title: RGZ-91 Re-GZ
info_text: The RGZ-91 Re-GZ (Refined Gundam Zeta) (リ·ガズィ Ri Gazi?) is a prototype transformable mobile suit, based on data from the MSZ-006R Zeta Plus R. The unit was featured in the anime movie Mobile Suit Gundam: Char's Counterattack and also featured in the OVA series Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn.

title: RGM-79[G] GM Ground Type
series: Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team
info_text: The RGM-79[G] GM Ground Type (陸戦型ジム) is a ground based predecessor to the RGM-79 GM. It first appeared in Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team.

title: AMX-004 Qubeley
info_text: AMX-004 Qubeley (キュベレイ Kyuberei?) is a mobile suit that appears in Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam and Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ. The unit is piloted by Haman Karn.

title: FA-010A FAZZ
info_text: The FA-010A FAZZ (pronounced as "fahts") is a variant of the MSZ-010 ΖΖ Gundam. The unit was featured in Gundam Sentinel.

title: MSZ-006A1 Zeta Plus A1 Test Color
info_text: The MSZ-006A1 Ζeta Plus A1 (Z Plus A1) is a part of the MSZ-006+ Zeta Plus line of mass-production mobile suits. The A1 type was the first mass-produced successor to the MSZ-006 Zeta Gundam. It was featured in the photo-novel Gundam Sentinel. The unit is piloted by Amuro Ray.

title: GF13-017NJII G Gundam
info_text: The GF13-017NJII God Gundam (aka G Gundam, Burning Gundam in the English dub) is the titular Mobile Fighter of Mobile Fighter G Gundam. It was the second Mobile Fighter used by Neo Japan in the 13th Gundam Fight, and is piloted by Domon Kasshu.

title: RX-77-2 Guncannon
info_text: The RX-77-2 Guncannon was the second mobile suit design model that stemmed from the Earth Federation's "Project V" in the Mobile Suit Gundam anime.

title: MSZ-006C1 Ζeta Plus C1
info_text: The MSZ-006C1 Ζ Plus C1 is a variant of the MSZ-006A1 Zeta Plus A1 designed for space combat. The unit is featured in the photo-novel Gundam Sentinel.

title: GF13-001NHII Master Gundam
info_text: The GF13-001NHII Master Gundam is a Mobile Fighter piloted by Master Asia. Representing Neo Hong Kong, it appeared in Mobile Fighter G Gundam and is one of the Four Heavenly Kings.

title: MS-06F2 Zaku II F2 Type (Zeon Version)
info_text: The MS-06F2 Zaku II F2 Type (aka Zaku II Late production model) is a mass-produced general purpose multi-class mobile suit and a variant of the original MS-06F Zaku II.

title: GF13-017NJ Shining Gundam
info_text: The GF13-017NJ Shining Gundam is a Mobile Fighter for the nation of Neo Japan built for the 13th Gundam Fight. It was featured in the anime Mobile Fighter G Gundam and is piloted by Domon Kasshu.

title: RGM-79C GM Type C Earth Type
info_text: The RGM-79C GM Type C (aka GM Kai) is an improved version of one of the Earth Federation Forces' first mass production mobile suit, the RGM-79(E) GM Early Type. It first appeared in Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory.

title: MSN-02 Zeong
info_text: The MSN-02 Zeong (ジオング Jiongu?) is a prototype mobile suit appearing in the anime Mobile Suit Gundam. Developed by the Principality of Zeon at the A Baoa Qu space fortress during the One Year War, it was built for Newtype pilots and was first piloted by the "Red Comet" Char Aznable.

title: RX-78/C.A. Gundam Char Aznable Custom
info_text: The RX-78/C.A. Gundam Char Aznable Custom is a mobile suit from the Universal Century timeline, which first appeared in the game Gihren's Greed.

title: GF13-021NG Gundam Spiegel
info_text: The GF13-021NG Gundam Spiegel (Shadow Gundam in the English dub) is a Mobile Fighter from Mobile Fighter G Gundam. It is piloted by Schwarz Bruder of Neo Germany.

title: MS-06F2 Zaku II F2 (E.F.S.F Version)
info_text: The MS-06F2 Zaku II F2 Type (aka Zaku II Late production model) is a mass-produced general purpose multi-class mobile suit and a variant of the original MS-06F Zaku II.

title: MSA-0011 S Gundam
info_text: The MSA-0011 (MSZ-011) S Gundam (aka Superior Gundam) was a prototype transformable mobile suit that appeared in the photo-novel Gundam Sentinel. The suit was originally called Supreme Gundam, but was also known under the codename "Ι Gundam" (Iota Gundam). The mobile suit is piloted by Ryou Roots.

title: RGM-79C GM Type C Space Type
info_text: The RGM-79C GM Type C (aka GM Kai) is an improved version of one of the Earth Federation Forces' first mass production mobile suit, the RGM-79(E) GM Early Type. It first appeared in Mobile Suit Gundam 0083: Stardust Memory.

title: RX-78-2 Gundam "Ver. Ka"
info_text: The RX-78-2 Gundam (aka the Gundam or White Mobile Suit) is the titular mobile suit of Mobile Suit Gundam. Part of the RX-78 Gundam series, it was built in secret on Side 7. The Gundam would turn the tide of war in favor of the Earth Federation during the One Year War against the Principality of Zeon. The unit was primarily piloted by the series' main protagonist Amuro Ray.

title: MS-09RS Rick Dom C.A. Custom
info_text: The MS-09RS Rick Dom C.A. Custom (also known simply as Char's Rick Dom) is a variant of the MS-09R Rick Dom, specially modified to Char Aznable's specifications. The unit is piloted by Char in the novelization of Mobile Suit Gundam, replacing the MSN-02 Zeong as Char's final mobile suit during the One Year War.

title: MS-14A Gelgoog (Anavel Gato Custom)
info_text: The MS-14A Gelgoog (ゲルググ,Gerugugu) was the last mass production mobile suit produced by the Principality of Zeon during the One Year War.

title: MSA-0011［Ext］ Ex-S Gundam
info_text: The MSA-0011[Ext] Ex-S Gundam (aka Extraordinary-Superior Gundam) is an upgraded version of the MSA-0011 S Gundam that appears in Gundam Sentinel. The mobile suit is piloted by Ryou Roots.

title: MSM-07 Z'Gok
info_text: The MSM-07 Z'Gok (ズゴック Zugokku?) is a mass production amphibious mobile suit. It was first featured in the anime series Mobile Suit Gundam, and later appeared in the OVA series Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn.

title: MSM-03 Gogg
info_text: The MSM-03 Gogg is a mass-produced amphibious mobile suit first featured in Mobile Suit Gundam.

title: RX-78-4 Gundam Unit 4 "G04"
series: Mobile Suit Gundam Side Story: Space, To the End of a Flash
info_text: The RX-78-4 Gundam Unit 4 (aka "G04") is a Gundam from Kunio Okawara's MS Collection (M-MSV) original design series, designed by Kunio Okawara as the 4th Gundam. The design was updated to be used in the video game Mobile Suit Gundam: Encounters In Space as well as the manga Mobile Suit Gundam Side Story: Space, To the End of a Flash.

title: RX-78-5 Gundam Unit 5 "G05"
series: Mobile Suit Gundam Side Story: Space, To the End of a Flash
info_text: The RX-78-5 Gundam Unit 5 (aka "G05") is a Gundam type mobile suit from Kunio Okawara's MS Collection (M-MSV) original design series, designed by Kunio Okawara as the 5th Gundam. The design was updated to be used in the video game Mobile Suit Gundam: Encounters In Space as well as the manga Mobile Suit Gundam Side Story: Space, To the End of a Flash.

title: GAT-X105+AQM/E-X01 Aile Strike Gundam
info_text: The GAT-X105+AQM/E-X01 Aile Strike is a prototype high mobility mobile suit, and is featured in Mobile Suit Gundam SEED. Its primary pilot was Kira Yamato before it was passed down to ace pilot Mu La Flaga.

title: MSM-07S Z'Gok Commander Type (Char Aznable custom)
info_text: The MSM-07S Z'Gok Commander Type is a variant of the MSM-07 Z'Gok created by the Principality of Zeon during the One Year War.

title: PF-78-1 Perfect Gundam
info_text: The PF-78-1 Perfect Gundam is a variation of the RX-78-2 Gundam, the titular mobile suit of Mobile Suit Gundam, and the first non-UC Gundam. Designed by Kunio Okawara and later by Hajime Katoki for the Gundam Fix Figuration version, it played a prominent part in the manga Plamo-Kyoshiro, and later became part of the original design series Mobile Suit Variations (MSV). Its built and piloted by Shiro Kyoda.

title: AMX-004-3 Qubeley Mk-II
info_text: The AMX-004 (AMX-005) Qubeley Mk-II (キュベレイMk-Ⅱ, Kyuberei Mk - Ⅱ) is the successor to the AMX-004 Qubeley featured in Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ. At least two units were built, piloted by Elpeo Ple and Ple Two respectively.

title: XXXG-01W Wing Gundam "Ver. Ka"
info_text: The XXXG-01W Wing Gundam (aka Wing Gundam or Gundam Zero-One) is the titular mobile suit of Mobile Suit Gundam Wing. It was developed in the L1 Colony Cluster by the engineer Doctor J as a tool to take revenge on the OZ organization for the assassination of the pacifist leader of the colonies, Heero Yuy. The unit was primarily piloted by the series' main protagonist Heero Yuy (a teenage boy who was code-named after the martryed pacifist).

title: RMS-099 Rick Dias
info_text: The RMS-099 Rick Dias (RMS-099 リック・ディアス Āru Emu Esu Zero Kyū Kyū Rikku Diasu?) is a second-generation mass production attack-use mobile suit featured in the Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam television series.

title: MSN-02 Perfect Zeong
info_text: The MSN-02 Perfect Zeong is a prototype Newtype-use mobile suit, and the completed version of the MSN-02 Zeong. It first appeared in Plamo-Kyoshiro, and later in the original design series Mobile Suit Variations (MSV) and the Mobile Suit Gundam: Char's Deleted Affair: Portrait Of Young Comet manga.

title: ZGMF-X10A Freedom Gundam
info_text: The ZGMF-X10A Freedom Gundam (aka Freedom, X10A) is a mobile suit that appears in Mobile Suit Gundam SEED and Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny. The unit is piloted by Kira Yamato.

title: RMS-106 Hi-Zack
info_text: The RMS-106 Hizack (aka Hi-Zack) is a mass-production general-purpose mobile suit featured in Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam. It was based on the MS-06 Zaku II mobile suits, and was used by EFSF groups, notably the Titans, during the Gryps War.

title: MBF-02 Strike Rouge
info_text: The MBF-02 Strike Rouge is a mobile suit appearing in Mobile Suit Gundam SEED and its sequel Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny. Its primary pilot is the Princess of Orb Cagalli Yula Athha. The word Rouge is the French word for the color red.

title: XXXG-00W0 Wing Gundam Zero EW
series: New Mobile Report Gundam Wing: Endless Waltz
info_text: The XXXG-00W0 Wing Gundam Zero (aka Wing Zero) is a mobile suit that is prominently featured in Mobile Suit Gundam Wing and its sequel OVA/movie Endless Waltz. Though having many pilots during its existence, the Gundam was most famously piloted by the series' main protagonist Heero Yuy.

title: RB-79 Ball "Ver. Ka"
info_text: The RB-79 Ball is a fictional weapon from the anime series Mobile Suit Gundam.

title: RMS-099 Rick Dias (Quattro Bajeena Custom)
info_text: The RMS-099 Rick Dias (RMS-099 リック・ディアス Āru Emu Esu Zero Kyū Kyū Rikku Diasu?) is a second-generation mass production attack-use mobile suit featured in the Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam television series.

title: RX-78-2 Gundam Ver. One Year War 0079
series: Mobile Suit Gundam: The One Year War
info_text: The RX-78-2 Gundam (aka the Gundam or White Mobile Suit) is the titular mobile suit of Mobile Suit Gundam. Part of the RX-78 Gundam series, it was built in secret on Side 7. The Gundam would turn the tide of war in favor of the Earth Federation during the One Year War against the Principality of Zeon. The unit was primarily piloted by the series' main protagonist Amuro Ray.

title: RB-79K Ball Type K
series: Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team
info_text: The RB-79K Ball Type K is a mobile pod featured in the OVA series Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team. It is piloted by Shiro Amada.

title: MSM-04 Acguy
info_text: The MSM-04 Acguy (アッガイ Aggai?) is a mass-produced amphibious mobile suit featured in the anime series Mobile Suit Gundam. It also appears in Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team and Mobile Suit Gundam Thunderbolt.

title: MSN-00100 Hyaku-Shiki + Ballute System
info_text: The MSN-00100 (MSN-100, MSN-001) Hyaku Shiki is a prototype attack use Mobile Suit from the Universal Century timeline. The unit was featured in Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam and Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ. It was primarily piloted by Quattro Bajeena during the Gryps Conflict and later Beecha Oleg in the First Neo Zeon War.

title: RX-178 Gundam Mk-II Ver. 2.0
info_text: The RX-178 Gundam Mk-II is a mobile suit that appears in the anime series Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam. It is a successor of the famous RX-78-2 Gundam that served in the One Year War with cheaper armor to reduce costs.

title: MSZ-006 Zeta Gundam Ver. 2.0
info_text:
The MSΖ-006 Zeta Gundam (MSΖ-006 Ζ
ゼータ
ガンダム?) is the titular mobile suit of the Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam television series and also featured in the Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ television series. It was most famously piloted by its designer, Kamille Bidan during the Gryps War.

title: MSA-003 Nemo
info_text: The MSA-003 Nemo is a mass-production attack-use mobile suit first featured in the anime series Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam. The design was later updated and featured in the light novel/OVA series Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn.

title: RX-178 Gundam Mk-II Ver. 2.0 (Titans)
info_text: The RX-178 Gundam Mk-II is a mobile suit that appears in the anime series Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam. It is a successor of the famous RX-78-2 Gundam that served in the One Year War with cheaper armor to reduce costs.

title: YMS-15 Gyan
info_text: The YMS-15 Gyan is a mobile suit from the anime series Mobile Suit Gundam.

title: F91 Gundam F91
info_text: The F91 Gundam F91 ("F91" standing for "Formula 91") is the titular mobile suit of Mobile Suit Gundam F91. The unit is piloted by Seabook Arno. Another F91, colored dark blue and yellow, is piloted by Harrison Martin.

title: RB-79 Ball (Shark Mouth)
info_text: The RB-79 Ball is a fictional weapon from the anime series Mobile Suit Gundam.

title: XM-X1 Crossbone Gundam X-1 "Ver. Ka"
info_text: XM-X1 Crossbone Gundam X-1 is a testbed mobile suit in the Universal Century developed by the Earth Federation's Strategic Naval Research Institute (SNRI). It was featured in the Mobile Suit Crossbone Gundam manga series.

title: GAT-X105 Strike Gundam + I.W.S.P.
series: Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Frame Astrays
info_text: The GAT-X105+P202QX Strike IWSP is a prototype mobile suit, it was featured in Mobile Suit Gundam SEED: Mobile Suit Variations.

title: F91 Gundam F91 (Harrison Martin Custom)
info_text: The F91 Gundam F91 ("F91" standing for "Formula 91") is the titular mobile suit of Mobile Suit Gundam F91. The unit is piloted by Seabook Arno. Another F91, colored dark blue and yellow, is piloted by Harrison Martin.

title: RGM-79[G] GM Sniper
series: Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team
info_text: The RGM-79[G] GM Sniper is a mass-produced ground long-range mobile suit, and is a variant to the RGM-79［G］ GM Ground Type. The unit is featured in the anime series Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team.

title: ZGMF-X20A Strike Freedom Gundam
info_text: The ZGMF-X20A Strike Freedom Gundam (aka Strike Freedom, Freedom) is the successor of the ZGMF-X10A Freedom. Appearing in Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny, it is piloted by Kira Yamato.

title: XM-X1 Crossbone Gundam X-1 Full Cloth
info_text: The XM-X1 Crossbone Gundam X-1 Full Cloth is a mobile suit which appears in the manga Mobile Suit Crossbone Gundam: Steel 7.

title: RX-93-ν2 Hi-ν Gundam
series: Mobile Suit Gundam: Char's Counterattack - Beltorchika's Children
info_text: The RX-93-ν2 Hi-ν Gundam (pronounced "High-New") is an alternate interpretation of the RX-93 ν Gundam which appears in Mobile Suit Gundam: Beltorchika's Children. It is piloted by Amuro Ray.

title: GAT-X105E+AQM/E-X09S Strike Noir Gundam
series: Mobile Suit Gundam SEED C.E. 73: STARGAZER
info_text: The GAT-X105E+AQME-X09S Strike Noir Gundam is a Mobile Suit that appears in the Mobile Suit Gundam SEED C.E. 73: STARGAZER OVA and the Mobile Suit Gundam SEED C.E. 73 Δ Astray manga. It is piloted by Sven Cal Bayang.

title: MS-06J Zaku II Ver. 2.0
info_text: The MS-06J Zaku II Ground Type is one of several variants of the MS-06 Zaku II line of Mobile Suits.

title: MS-06S Zaku II Commander Type (Char Aznable Custom) Ver. 2.0
info_text: The MS-06S Zaku II Commander Type is a Mobile Suit introduced in the Mobile Suit Gundam television series. This variant looks very similar to the standard MS-06F Zaku II, so much so, that the Earth Federation can generally only tell the difference from color schemes most pilots apply to their units and the increased performance of this version.

title: MS-14S Gelgoog Commander Type (Char Aznable Custom) Ver. 2.0
info_text: The MS-14S (YMS-14) Gelgoog Commander Type is a commander mobile suit that entered production as the MS-14A Gelgoog.

title: WD-M01 ∀ Gundam
info_text: The SYSTEM ∀-99 ∀ Gundam (pronounced "Turn A Gundam", aka "∀", "White Doll", "White Devil", "Mustache") is the titular mobile suit of Turn A Gundam. It is piloted primarily by Loran Cehack.

title: ZGMF-X42S Destiny Gundam
info_text: The ZGMF-X42S Destiny Gundam is the titular mobile suit of Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny. This unit was piloted by Shinn Asuka during the Second Alliance-PLANT War

title: RX-0 Unicorn Gundam Ver. Ka
info_text: The RX-0 Unicorn Gundam (ユニコーン ガンダム Yunikōn Gandamu?, or Unicorn Gundam, Unicorn, RX-0) is the titular prototype mobile suit of the Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn novel, its OVA adaptation and the television re-cut. Developed by Anaheim Electronics for the Earth Federation, the machine concealed a secret that could shake the future of all humanity,[1] for it was the key to opening Laplace's Box. The suit is piloted by Banagher Links after the head of the Vist Foundation and his father, Cardeas Vist, entrusted it to him at the dawn of the Third Neo Zeon War in U.C. 0096.[2]

title: MS-06R-1A Zaku II Ver.2.0 (Black Tri-Stars Version)
info_text: The MS-06R-1A Zaku II High Mobility Type is a mobile suit first appearing in Mobile Suit Variations for Mobile Suit Gundam III: Encounters in Space. It is a mass-production space combat mobile suit, and one of many variants of the standard MS-06 Zaku II.

title: GAT-X105E Lukas's Strike E + I.W.S.P.
series: Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Frame Astrays
info_text: The Strike Gundam E IWSP is a Mobile Suit in the Cosmic Era timeline. It is piloted by Sven Cal Payang and Lukas O'Donnell.

title: MS-06F Zaku Minelayer
info_text: The MS-06F Zaku Minelayer is a mine layer mobile suit and is a variant of the original MS-06F Zaku II. It was first featured in the original design series Mobile Suit Variations (MSV).

title: MS-06F Zaku II Ver. 2.0
info_text: The MS-06F Zaku II is one of many variants of the MS-06 Zaku II series of Mobile Suits. The MS-06F was the most produced mobile suit during the One Year War, with 3,246 units built during the war. The MS-06F was piloted by top-scoring Zeon MS aces, as well as by the highest-scoring Zeon ace in the war. It first appears in the anime series Mobile Suit Gundam.

title: MS-14A Gelgoog Ver. 2.0
info_text: The MS-14A Gelgoog (ゲルググ,Gerugugu) was the last mass production mobile suit produced by the Principality of Zeon during the One Year War.

title: GAT-X105+AQM/E-X03 Launcher Strike Gundam/GAT-X105+AQM/E-X02 Sword Strike Gundam
info_text: The GAT-X105+AQM/E-X03 Launcher Strike is a prototype heavy assault mobile suit, it is featured in the anime Mobile Suit Gundam SEED. Its primary pilot was Kira Yamato before it was passed down to ace pilot Mu La Flaga.

title: ZGMF-X56S/α Force Impulse Gundam
info_text: The ZGMF-X56S/α Force Impulse Gundam is a Mobile Suit featured in the Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny television series. It is analogous to the Earth Alliance's GAT-X105+AQM/E-X01 Aile Strike Gundam. It is piloted by Shinn Asuka and later by Lunamaria Hawke.

title: Shin Musha Gundam
info_text: Musha Gundam is one of the titular Mobile Suit from the series Plamo-Kyoshiro, which then got a separate franchise starting with SD Sengokuden Musha Shichinin Shuu Hen. The SD version is designed by Koichi Yamato and Craft dan representative, Yasui Hisashi while the Dynasty Warriors Gundam version is designed by Hajime Katoki. Although the concept began with more typical Gundam proportions, the idea is most famous for inspiring the long running SD Gundam franchise.

title: RX-78-2 Gundam Ver. 2.0
info_text: The RX-78-2 Gundam (aka the Gundam or White Mobile Suit) is the titular mobile suit of Mobile Suit Gundam. Part of the RX-78 Gundam series, it was built in secret on Side 7. The Gundam would turn the tide of war in favor of the Earth Federation during the One Year War against the Principality of Zeon. The unit was primarily piloted by the series' main protagonist Amuro Ray.

title: MS-06K Zaku Cannon
info_text: The MS-06K Zaku Cannon is a mass-produced artillery test type mobile suit. It was one of many variants of the standard MS-06 Zaku II produced by the Principality of Zeon during the One Year War. The unit is featured in the original design series Mobile Suit Variations and Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn novel/OVA.

title: MS-06R-2 Zaku II Ver. 2.0 (Johnny Ridden Custom)
info_text: The MS-06R-2 Zaku II High Mobility Type is a limited production space combat mobile suit, and is another high mobility version of the MS-06 Zaku II. It was first featured in the original design series Mobile Suit Variations (MSV).

title: ZGMF-X19A ∞ Justice Gundam
info_text: The ZGMF-X19A ∞ Justice Gundam (aka Infinite Justice, ∞ Justice) is a mobile suit as well as the successor to ZGMF-X09A Justice Gundam and appears in Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny. The unit is mainly piloted by Athrun Zala.

title: MS-06R-1A Zaku II Ver. 2.0 (Shin Matsunaga Custom)
info_text: The MS-06R-1A Zaku II High Mobility Type is a mobile suit first appearing in Mobile Suit Variations for Mobile Suit Gundam III: Encounters in Space. It is a mass-production space combat mobile suit, and one of many variants of the standard MS-06 Zaku II.

title: MSN-06S Sinanju "Ver. Ka"
info_text: The MSN-06S Sinanju (aka Sinanju, MSN-06S) is a mobile suit featured in the Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn novel, its OVA adaptation and the television re-cut. It is the modified version of Anaheim Electronics's MSN-06S Sinanju Stein. It was piloted by Full Frontal during the Third Neo Zeon War.

title: G-Fighter
info_text: The G-Fighter is a space and atmospheric fighter. It is the support unit to the RX-78-2 Gundam. It was featured in the original Mobile Suit Gundam TV series.

title: RGM-79 GM Ver. 2.0
info_text: The RGM-79 GM (aka GM, pronounced Jim) was the first mass-produced mobile suit of the Earth Federation. It first appears in Mobile Suit Gundam.

title: ZGMF-X56S/β Sword Impulse Gundam
info_text: The ZGMF-X56S/β Sword Impulse Gundam is a Mobile Suit in the series Gundam SEED Destiny, and is analogous to the Earth Alliance's old GAT-X105+AQM/E-X02 Sword Strike. It is piloted by Shinn Asuka and later by Lunamaria Hawke.

title: MS-07B Gouf Ver. 2.0
info_text: The MS-07B Gouf is a mass production ground close-quarters combat mobile suit. It was first featured in the anime series Mobile Suit Gundam.

title: "G-Armor" Realtype Color
info_text: The G-Armor is one of the combined forms of the RX-78-2 Gundam and its support unit, the G-Fighter. This configuration uses a standard RX-78-2 (sans weapons) equipped with two shields, with the top section covered by G Part A and the bottom section covered by G-Part B. This is the mainstay form of the Gundam and G-Fighter due to the quick docking/undocking sequence.

title: MS-06J Zaku Ver. 2.0 "White Ogre"
series: Mobile Suit Gundam MS IGLOO 2: The Gravity Front
info_text: The MS-06J Zaku II Ground Type is one of several variants of the MS-06 Zaku II line of Mobile Suits.

title: GN-001 Gundam Exia
info_text: The GN-001 Gundam Exia (aka Exia, Gundam Seven Swords), is the close combat Gundam-type mobile suit featured in both seasons of Mobile Suit Gundam 00. The unit is piloted by Setsuna F. Seiei.

title: RX-75-4 Guntank
info_text: The RX-75-4 Guntank is a mobile suit in the series Mobile Suit Gundam.

title: MBF-P03R Gundam Astray Blue Frame 2nd Revise
series: Mobile Suit Gundam SEED VS Astray
info_text: The MBF-P03R Gundam Astray Blue Frame 2nd Revise is the improved form of the MBF-P03 Gundam Astray Blue Frame Second L developed by the Serpent Tail with help from Lowe Guele. It first appeared in photo series Mobile Suit Gundam SEED VS Astray. The unit is piloted by Gai Murakumo.

title: AMX-004-2 Qubeley Mk-II
info_text: The AMX-004 (AMX-005) Qubeley Mk-II (キュベレイMk-Ⅱ, Kyuberei Mk - Ⅱ) is the successor to the AMX-004 Qubeley featured in Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ. At least two units were built, piloted by Elpeo Ple and Ple Two respectively.

title: LM312V04/06 Victory Gundam "Ver. Ka"
info_text: The LM312V04 Victory Gundam is the titular mobile suit of Mobile Suit Victory Gundam, most prominently piloted by Uso Ewin until he acquired its successor, the LM314V21 Victory 2 Gundam.

title: RX-78-3 Gundam "G-3" Ver. 2.0
info_text: The RX-78-3 Gundam "G-3" is a variation of the original RX-78-2 Gundam. It first appeared as part of Mobile Suit Variations model kit series, designed by Kunio Okawara and later reappeared in the game Gundam Battle Universe and Gundam the Ride: A Baoa Qu.

title: GNX-603T GN-X
info_text: The GNX-603T GN-X (aka GN-X, pronounced "Jinx") is a series of mass production mobile suits used by the United Nations Forces in season 1 of Mobile Suit Gundam 00.

title: MBF-P02Kai Gundam Astray Red Frame Kai
series: Mobile Suit Gundam SEED VS Astray
info_text: The Astray Red Frame Kai is the upgraded version of the MBF-P02 Gundam Astray Red Frame developed and piloted by Lowe Guele. It first appeared in the photo series Mobile Suit Gundam SEED VS Astray.

title: RX-0 Unicorn Gundam OVA Ver.
info_text: The RX-0 Unicorn Gundam (ユニコーン ガンダム Yunikōn Gandamu?, or Unicorn Gundam, Unicorn, RX-0) is the titular prototype mobile suit of the Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn novel, its OVA adaptation and the television re-cut. Developed by Anaheim Electronics for the Earth Federation, the machine concealed a secret that could shake the future of all humanity,[1] for it was the key to opening Laplace's Box. The suit is piloted by Banagher Links after the head of the Vist Foundation and his father, Cardeas Vist, entrusted it to him at the dawn of the Third Neo Zeon War in U.C. 0096.[2]

title: XXXG-01W Wing Gundam
info_text: The XXXG-01W Wing Gundam (aka Wing Gundam or Gundam Zero-One) is the titular mobile suit of Mobile Suit Gundam Wing. It was developed in the L1 Colony Cluster by the engineer Doctor J as a tool to take revenge on the OZ organization for the assassination of the pacifist leader of the colonies, Heero Yuy. The unit was primarily piloted by the series' main protagonist Heero Yuy (a teenage boy who was code-named after the martryed pacifist).

title: Musha Gundam Mk. II
info_text: Musha Gundam Mk-II is the variant of the Musha Gundam from SD Sengokuden Musha Shichinin Shuu Hen and Dynasty Warriors Gundam. The SD version is designed by Koichi Yamato and Craft dan representative, Yasui Hisashi while the Dynasty Warriors Gundam version is designed by Hajime Katoki.

title: FA-78-1 Full Armor Gundam
info_text: The FA-78-1 Gundam Full Armor Type (aka Full Armor Gundam and Perfect Gundam II) is a Mobile Suit and variant of the RX-78-2 Gundam equipped with external armor. It is featured in the original design series Mobile Suit Variation.

title: LM312V04(B-part)+SD-VB03A Core Booster "Ver. Ka"
info_text: The LM312V04+SD-VB03A V-Dash Gundam is a variant of the LM312V04 Victory Gundam featured in Mobile Suit Victory Gundam. It is piloted by Uso Ewin.

title: LM312V04+SD-VB03A V-Dash Gundam "Ver. Ka"
info_text: The LM312V04+SD-VB03A V-Dash Gundam is a variant of the LM312V04 Victory Gundam featured in Mobile Suit Victory Gundam. It is piloted by Uso Ewin.

title: PMX-003 The-O
info_text: The PMX-003 The-O is a mobile suit from the series Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam. The unit is piloted by Paptimus Scirocco.

title: XXXG-01D Gundam Deathscythe EW
series: New Mobile Report Gundam Wing: Endless Waltz
info_text: The XXXG-01D Gundam Deathscythe (aka Deathscythe or Gundam Zero-Two), is the second of five Gundams sent down to Earth from the Space Colonies in New Mobile Report Gundam Wing. It was piloted by Duo Maxwell.

title: RGZ-95 ReZEL
info_text: The RGZ-95 ReZEL is a mass-production transformable mobile suit. It is featured in the novel and OVA version of Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn. One of these units is piloted by Riddhe Marcenas.

title: GNT-0000 00 Qan[T]
series: Mobile Suit Gundam 00 The Movie -A wakening of the Trailblazer-
info_text: The GNT-0000 00 Qan[T] (aka 00Q, 00 Qan[T], pronounced "Double-Oh Quanta"), is the successor unit to the GN-0000+GNR-010 00 Raiser in Mobile Suit Gundam 00 The Movie -A wakening of the Trailblazer-. The unit is piloted by Setsuna F. Seiei.

title: RGZ-95C ReZEL Commander Type
info_text: The RGZ-95C ReZEL Commander Type (aka ReZEL Type C) is a mass-produced commander's variant of the RGZ-95 ReZEL. It is featured in the novel and OVA version of the Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn. One of these units is piloted by Norm Basilicock.

title: XXXG-01D2 Gundam Deathscythe Hell EW
series: New Mobile Report Gundam Wing: Endless Waltz
info_text: The XXXG-01D2 Gundam Deathscythe Hell (aka Deathscythe Hell, or Gundam Zero-Two), is the upgraded version of XXXG-01D Gundam Deathscythe in Mobile Suit Gundam Wing. The suit was redesigned by Hajime Katoki for the movie sequel New Mobile Report Gundam Wing: Endless Waltz. The unit is piloted by Duo Maxwell.

title: XXXG-01S Shenlong Gundam EW
series: New Mobile Report Gundam Wing: Endless Waltz
info_text: The XXXG-01S Shenlong Gundam (aka Shenlong, Nataku, or Gundam Zero-Five) is mobile suit featured in Mobile Suit Gundam Wing. Piloted by Chang Wufei, the unit was later upgraded into Altron Gundam.

title: XXXG-01W Wing Gundam EW
series: New Mobile Report Gundam Wing: Endless Waltz
info_text: The XXXG-01W Wing Gundam (aka Wing Gundam or Gundam Zero-One) is the titular mobile suit of Mobile Suit Gundam Wing. It was developed in the L1 Colony Cluster by the engineer Doctor J as a tool to take revenge on the OZ organization for the assassination of the pacifist leader of the colonies, Heero Yuy. The unit was primarily piloted by the series' main protagonist Heero Yuy (a teenage boy who was code-named after the martryed pacifist).

title: GN-0000+GNR-010 00 Raiser
info_text: The GN-0000+GNR-010 00 Raiser (aka 00 Raiser, 00R), is the combined and mainstay form of GN-0000 00 Gundam and GNR-010 0 Raiser in mid-season 2 of Mobile Suit Gundam 00. The unit is co-piloted by Setsuna F. Seiei piloting the 00 Gundam and Saji Crossroad piloting the Raiser, however, when combined Setsuna can operate it himself.

title: OZ-13MS Gundam Epyon EW
series: New Mobile Report Gundam Wing: Endless Waltz
info_text: The OZ-13MS Gundam Epyon is a mobile suit featured in Mobile Suit Gundam Wing. Originally piloted by Heero Yuy, the suit would later be given to Zechs Merquise.

title: MSN-001A1 Delta Plus
info_text: The MSN-001A1 Delta Plus (aka δ Plus) is a prototype transformable mobile suit and the variant of the MSN-001 Delta Gundam which appears in the novel and OVA Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn. The unit is piloted by Riddhe Marcenas.

title: GN-0000GNHW/7SG 00 Gundam Seven Sword/G
info_text: The GN-0000GNHW/7SG 00 Gundam Seven Sword/G (aka 00 Gundam Seven Sword/G, 00 Seven Sword G), is a variant of the GN-0000/7S 00 Gundam Seven Sword. This unit is piloted by Setsuna F. Seiei. It first appears in Mobile Suit Gundam 00V: Battlefield Record.

title: XXXG-01SR Gundam Sandrock EW
series: New Mobile Report Gundam Wing: Endless Waltz
info_text: The XXXG-0SR Gundam Sandrock (aka Sandrock or Gundam Zero-Four) is a close quarters mobile suit, it is featured in the anime series Mobile Suit Gundam Wing. The unit is piloted by Quatre Raberba Winner.

title: RX-0 Full Armor Unicorn Gundam "Ver. Ka"
info_text: The RX-0 Full Armor Unicorn Gundam (aka Full Armor Unicorn, Unicorn) is the RX-0 Unicorn Gundam equipped with an array of weapons. It is piloted by Banagher Links.

title: XXXG-01H Gundam Heavyarms EW
series: New Mobile Report Gundam Wing: Endless Waltz
info_text: The XXXG-01H Gundam Heavyarms (aka Heavyarms or Gundam Zero-Three) is a mobile suit from the series Mobile Suit Gundam WIng. It was the third of Operation Meteor's five Gundams. Gundam Heavyarms was piloted by a young man operating under the pseudonym Trowa Barton.

title: GAT-X102 Duel Gundam w/ Assault Shroud
info_text: The GAT-X102 Duel Gundam is the first mobile suit developed under the Earth Alliance's "G Project" in the Cosmic Era timeline. It was featured in the series Mobile Suit Gundam SEED.

title: AGE-1 Gundam AGE-1 Normal
info_text: The AGE-1 Gundam AGE-1 Normal is one of four titular mobile suits featured in the Flit Arc and Asemu Arc of the Mobile Suit Gundam AGE anime series. The unit was mainly piloted by Flit Asuno and later, it was temporarily piloted by Asemu Asuno.

title: AGE-1T Gundam AGE-1 Titus
info_text: The AGE-1T Gundam AGE-1 Titus (aka Titus) is a close combat variant of the AGE-1 Gundam AGE-1 Normal from the Mobile Suit Gundam AGE anime series. It is piloted by Flit Asuno.

title: RX-0 Unicorn Gundam 02 Banshee
info_text: The RX-0 Unicorn Gundam 02 Banshee (aka Banshee) is a mobile suit that appears in Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn. It is the sister unit of the RX-0 Unicorn Gundam, built alongside the Unicorn under the Earth Federation's UC Project. it was originally piloted by Marida Cruz, but was later assigned to Riddhe Marcenas (in the novel only).

title: AGE-1S Gundam AGE-1 Spallow
info_text: The AGE-1S Gundam AGE-1 Spallow is a high-speed combat variant of the AGE-1 Gundam AGE-1 Normal from the anime series Mobile Suit Gundam AGE. The unit is primary piloted by Flit Asuno.

title: RMS-108 Marasai
info_text: The RMS-108 Marasai, also known as the MSA-002 Marasai is a second-generation mobile suit in the Universal Century timeline. It first appeared in the series Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam.

title: GAT-X207 Blitz Gundam
info_text: The GAT-X207 Blitz Gundam is a Mobile Suit featured in Mobile Suit Gundam SEED. The unit is piloted by Nicol Amalfi.

title: AGE-2 Gundam AGE-2 Normal
info_text: The AGE-2 Gundam AGE-2 Normal is the successor of the AGE-1 Gundam AGE-1 Normal, appearing in the Asemu Arc of Mobile Suit Gundam AGE. The unit is piloted by Asemu Asuno.

title: GAT-X103 Buster Gundam
info_text: The GAT-X103 Buster Gundam is a prototype artillery mobile suit, the unit is featured in the anime series Mobile Suit Gundam SEED.

title: GAT-X303 Aegis Gundam
info_text: The GAT-X303 Aegis Gundam is a prototype transformable mobile weapon, it is featured in the anime series Mobile Suit Gundam SEED. The unit is piloted by Athrun Zala.

title: AGE-2DH Gundam AGE-2 Dark Hound
info_text: The AGE-2DH Gundam AGE-2 Dark Hound is the modified version of the AGE-2 Gundam AGE-2 Normal first featured in the manga Mobile Suit Gundam AGE: Memories of Sid and the Kio Arc and Three Generation Arc of Mobile Suit Gundam AGE. The unit is piloted by the leader of the Space Pirates Bisidian, Captain Ash.

title: RX-93 ν Gundam "Ver. Ka"
info_text: The RX-93 ν Gundam (aka Nu Gundam, Nu) is a mobile suit that appears in Mobile Suit Gundam: Char's Counterattack. It was designed and piloted by Amuro Ray.

title: OZ-00MS Tallgeese EW
series: New Mobile Report Gundam Wing: Endless Waltz
info_text: The OZ-00MS Tallgeese (aka Tallgeese) is the first in a line of three mobile suits depicted in the Mobile Suit Gundam Wing series. In the anime, it is stated that the first Tallgeese was the original armed mobile suit, and is the common ancestor of both the Gundams (specifically their prototype, the XXXG-00W0 Wing Gundam Zero) and the mass-produced military mobile suits (most notably the OZ-06MS Leo and its variants) depicted. It was first test piloted after its restoration by an OZ soldier named Otto, and later by its most prominent pilot, Zechs Merquise.

title: MSN-06S Sinanju Stein "Ver. Ka"
info_text: The MSN-06S Sinanju Stein (aka Sinanju Stein) is a mobile suit featured in the PlayStation 3 video game Mobile Suit Gundam UC and UC-MSV. It is the successor unit to Char Aznable's MSN-04 Sazabi.

title: MSN-06S Sinanju (OVA Ver.)
info_text: The MSN-06S Sinanju (aka Sinanju, MSN-06S) is a mobile suit featured in the Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn novel, its OVA adaptation and the television re-cut. It is the modified version of Anaheim Electronics's MSN-06S Sinanju Stein. It was piloted by Full Frontal during the Third Neo Zeon War.

title: RGM-96X Jesta
info_text: The RGM-96X Jesta is a specialized escort and special operations mobile suit featured in Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn. The RGM-96X is based on the RGM-89 Jegan and is used by the Earth Federation.

title: GAT-X105+AQM/E-X01 Aile Strike Gundam (Ver. RM)
info_text: The GAT-X105+AQM/E-X01 Aile Strike is a prototype high mobility mobile suit, and is featured in Mobile Suit Gundam SEED. Its primary pilot was Kira Yamato before it was passed down to ace pilot Mu La Flaga.

title: AGE-2DB Gundam AGE-2 Double Bullet
info_text: The AGE-2DB Gundam AGE-2 Double Bullet is the second wear configuration of the AGE-2 Gundam AGE-2 Normal appearing in the Mobile Suit Gundam AGE anime series. The unit is piloted by Asemu Asuno.

title: AMS-119 Geara Doga
info_text: The AMS-119 Geara Doga is a mass-production general-purpose mobile suit featured in Mobile Suit Gundam: Char's Counterattack and Mobile Suit Gundam Unicorn.

title: RX-78-2 Gundam Ver.3.0
info_text: The RX-78-2 Gundam (aka the Gundam or White Mobile Suit) is the titular mobile suit of Mobile Suit Gundam. Part of the RX-78 Gundam series, it was built in secret on Side 7. The Gundam would turn the tide of war in favor of the Earth Federation during the One Year War against the Principality of Zeon. The unit was primarily piloted by the series' main protagonist Amuro Ray.

title: MBF-02+EW454F Strike Rouge + Ootori (Ver. RM)
info_text: The MBF-02+EW454F Strike Rouge Ootori is a variant of MBF-02 Strike Rouge and was exclusively featured in the Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny HD Remaster. The unit is primary piloted by the Princess of Orb, Cagalli Yula Athha.

title: XXXG-00W0 Wing Gundam Proto Zero EW
series: New Mobile Report Gundam Wing: Endless Waltz
info_text: The XXXG-00W0 Wing Gundam Zero (aka Wing Zero) is a mobile suit that is prominently featured in Mobile Suit Gundam Wing and its sequel OVA/movie Endless Waltz. Though having many pilots during its existence, the Gundam was most famously piloted by the series' main protagonist Heero Yuy.

title: MSN-04 Sazabi "Ver. Ka"
info_text: The MSN-04 Sazabi is a mobile suit that appears in Mobile Suit Gundam: Char's Counterattack. It is piloted by Char Aznable.

title: GAT-X105B/FP Build Strike Gundam Full Package
info_text: The GAT-X105B/FP Build Strike Gundam Full Package is a Gunpla from the anime series Gundam Build Fighters. It's built by Sei Iori and primary controlled by Reiji.

title: GX-9900 Gundam X
info_text: The GX-9900 Gundam X (aka Gundam X, GX, X) is a mass-produced mobile suit built by the former United Nations Earth, as well as the titular mobile suit of After War Gundam X. There are two feature versions of Gundam X. The primary featured one was piloted by Garrod Ran and later by Jamil Neate, after it was badly damaged in combat and was repaired and rebuilt as GX-9900-DV Gundam X Divider.

title: 侍ノ弐 Sengoku Astray Gundam
info_text: The 侍ノ弐 Sengoku Astray Gundam (戦国アストレイ頑駄無 Sengoku Asutorei Gandamu?) is a mobile suit appearing in the anime series Gundam Build Fighters. Based on the MBF-P02 Gundam Astray Red Frame, the Gunpla is built and controlled by Nils Nielsen.

title: RX-0 Unicorn Gundam 03 Phenex
series: Mobile Suit Gundam UC: One of Seventy Two
info_text: The RX-0 Unicorn Gundam 03 Phenex[1] is a mobile suit that appeared in Mobile Suit Gundam UC: One of Seventy Two. It also makes an appearance in the manga Mobile Suit Gundam U.C. 0096: Last Sun and the Mobile Suit Gundam UC: Phoenix Hunter novel.

title: RX-178B Build Gundam Mk-II
info_text: The RX-178B Build Gundam Mk-II is a Gunpla from the anime series Gundam Build Fighters and a variant of the RX-178 Gundam Mk-II. It is built by Sei Iori as a backup unit, and is piloted by Reiji, and later by Sei himself.

title: UB-01 Universe Booster
info_text: The GAT-X105B/ST Star Build Strike Gundam is a Gunpla featured in Gundam Build Fighters, it is an upgraded version of the GAT-X105B/FP Build Strike Gundam Full Package. It's built by Sei Iori and primarily controlled by Reiji.

title: CONCEPT-X 6-1-2 Turn X
info_text: The CONCEPT-X 6-1-2 Turn X (aka Turn X) is a mobile suit featured in Turn A Gundam. It is piloted by Gym Ghingham.

title: RX-93-ν2 Hi-ν Gundam "Ver. Ka"
series: Mobile Suit Gundam: Char's Counterattack - Beltorchika's Children
info_text: The RX-93-ν2 Hi-ν Gundam (pronounced "High-New") is an alternate interpretation of the RX-93 ν Gundam which appears in Mobile Suit Gundam: Beltorchika's Children. It is piloted by Amuro Ray.

title: MBF-P03D Gundam Astray Blue Frame D
series: Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny Astray B
info_text: The MBF-P03D Gundam Astray Blue Frame D is a variant of the Gundam Astray Blue Frame Second L/G in the novel Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny Astray B. It is piloted by Gai Murakumo.

title: PPGN-001 Gundam Exia Dark Matter
info_text: The PPGN-001 Gundam Exia Dark Matter is a Gunpla from the Gundam Build Fighters anime. A modified version of the PPGN-001 Gundam Amazing Exia, it is controlled by Meijin Kawaguchi.

title: GX-9901-DX Gundam Double X
info_text: The GX-9901-DX Gundam Double X (aka Gundam DX, Double X, DX) is a mobile suit produced by the New United Nations Earth in After War Gundam X, piloted by Garrod Ran.

title: MSN-00100 Hyaku Shiki Ver. 2.0
info_text: The MSN-00100 (MSN-100, MSN-001) Hyaku Shiki is a prototype attack use Mobile Suit from the Universal Century timeline. The unit was featured in Mobile Suit Zeta Gundam and Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ. It was primarily piloted by Quattro Bajeena during the Gryps Conflict and later Beecha Oleg in the First Neo Zeon War.

title: XXXG-01Wfr Gundam Fenice Rinascita
info_text: The XXXG-01Wfr Gundam Fenice Rinascita is a custom Gunpla and the successor of the XXXG-01Wf Wing Gundam Fenice from the anime series, Gundam Build Fighters. The Gunpla is modeled and primary controlled by Ricardo Fellini.

title: PF-78-3A Gundam Amazing Red Warrior
info_text: The PF-78-3A Gundam Amazing Red Warrior is a Gunpla from the anime series Gundam Build Fighters Try. It is a variant of the PF-78-3 Perfect Gundam III.

title: RX-78-02 Gundam The Origin
info_text: The RX-78-02 Gundam (RX-78-02 ガンダム?) is the titular mobile suit of the Mobile Suit Gundam: The Origin manga. It was piloted by Amuro Ray during the One Year War.

title: LM314V21 Victory Two Gundam "Ver.Ka"
info_text: The LM314V21 Victory 2 Gundam (aka Victory 2, V2, LM314V21) is the successor of the LM312V04 Victory Gundam featured in Mobile Suit Victory Gundam. It is piloted by Uso Ewin.

title: ZGMF-X10A Freedom Gundam Ver. 2.0
info_text: The ZGMF-X10A Freedom Gundam (aka Freedom, X10A) is a mobile suit that appears in Mobile Suit Gundam SEED and Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Destiny. The unit is piloted by Kira Yamato.

title: FA-78 Full Armor Gundam [Gundam Thunderbolt] "Ver.Ka"
info_text: The FA-78 Full Armor Gundam is a prototype mobile suit from the Mobile Suit Gundam Thunderbolt series. It is piloted by Io Fleming.

title: MS-06R Zaku II High Mobility Type "Psycho Zaku" [Gundam Thunderbolt] "Ver.Ka"
info_text: The MS-06R Zaku High Mobility Type (Reuse "P" Device) is a prototype mobile suit from Mobile Suit Gundam Thunderbolt. It is piloted by Daryl Lorenz.

title: RGM-79SP GM Sniper II
series: Mobile Suit Gundam 0080: War in the Pocket
info_text: The RGM-79SP GM Sniper II is a variant of the mass production RGM-79 GM. It first appeared in Mobile Suit Gundam 0080: War in the Pocket.

title: ZGMF-X13A Providence Gundam
info_text: The ZGMF-X13A Providence Gundam is a mobile suit in the series Mobile Suit Gundam SEED. It is piloted by Rau Le Creuset.

title: ZGMF-X09A Justice Gundam
info_text: The ZGMF-X09A Justice Gundam is a mobile suit featured in Mobile Suit Gundam SEED, piloted by Athrun Zala.

title: MSZ-010 ZZ Gundam "Ver.Ka"
info_text: The MSZ-010 ΖΖ Gundam (aka ΖΖ Gundam, ZZ, MSZ-010; pronounced "Double Zeta") is the titular mobile suit of the anime Mobile Suit Gundam ZZ. It is piloted by Judau Ashta.

title: RGM-79SC GM Sniper Custom
info_text: The RGM-79SC GM Sniper Custom is a variant of the mass production RGM-79 GM. It was first featured in the original design series Mobile Suit Variations (MSV).
